{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in the left part of the Fig. 5, we present the 20 most important features for the hypertension prediction.",
    "Each feature is assigned a score that signifies its relative importance in the prediction model.",
    "If there is a prior occurrence of this feature, the risk of target disease will be higher.",
    "Higher scores imply a stronger relationship with the occurrence of hypertension.",
    "The most influential feature is coded as 773.1, corresponding to hemolytic disease due to ABO isoimmunization, which could possibly indirect cause the hypertension due to compensatory cardiovascular responses, fluid overload, etc."
  ]
}